{
  "texts": [
    "Besides, the explainability made possible through Grad-CAM visualizations will help clinicians to understand the decision-making process of the model, thereby further increasing trust and usability in clinical practice.",
    "The proposed PolynetDWTCADx framework shows an excellent step toward the automation of colorectal cancer detection and segmentation.",
    "Incorporating CNN for feature extraction, DWT for refinement of features, SVM for robust classification, and U-Net for accurate segmentation, the obtained framework showed an accuracy of 92.3% testing in accuracy, Dice Coefficient of 0.96, and IoU of 0.93.",
    "These results highlight the fact that the framework effectively addresses the dual problems of classification and segmentation, while making it clinically more useful for clinical decision support in colonoscopy workflows.",
    "Qualitative and quantitative assessments together endorse the framework's ability to enhance diagnostic accuracy, reduce observer variability, and thus improve patient outcomes."
  ]
}